This paper deals with optimization problems in high dimensional space, which is a common topic in computer science. The focus on clustering and SVM suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of JL transform, a popular method for dimension reduction, also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), as these fields often deal with high dimensional data. Finally, the use of novel insights in geometry suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), as this field often involves geometric optimization problems.
